Thermal stresses

Δ L = 1 E F A L 0 L 0 = Δ L α Δ T F A = α E Δ T Δ L = 1 E F A L 0 L 0 = Δ L α Δ T F A = α E Δ T {:[Delta L=(1)/(E)(F)/(A)L_(0)],[L_(0)=(Delta L)/(alpha Delta T)],[(F)/(A)=alpha E Delta T]:}\begin{gather*} \Delta L =\frac{1}{E} \frac{F}{A} L_0\\ L_0 = \frac{\Delta L}{\alpha \Delta T}\\ \frac{F}{A} = \alpha E \Delta T \end{gather*}ΔL=1EFAL0L0=ΔLαΔTFA=αEΔTStartLayout 1st Row normal upper Delta upper L equals StartFraction 1 Over upper E EndFraction StartFraction upper F Over upper A EndFraction upper L 0 2nd Row upper L 0 equals StartFraction normal upper Delta upper L Over alpha normal upper Delta upper T EndFraction 3rd Row StartFraction upper F Over upper A EndFraction equals alpha upper E normal upper Delta upper T EndLayout
where E is Young's modulus (explained below) of the material

Stress 应力 σ σ sigma\sigmaσsigma

Stress σ σ sigma\sigmaσsigma is the force per unit area (就是pressure) causing the deformation.
单位是 P a P a PaPaPaupper P a.
1 P a = 1 N / m 2 1 P a = 1 N / m 2 1Pa=1N//m^(2)1 Pa = 1 N/m^21Pa=1N/m21 upper P a equals 1 upper N divided by m squared
Elastic modulus constant of proportionality 杨式模量
For sufficiently small stresses, stress应力 is proportional to strain应变, with the constant of proportionality depending on the material being deformed and on the nature of the deformation.
E = σ ε E = σ ε E=(sigma )/(epsi)E = \frac{\sigma}{\varepsilon}E=σεupper E equals StartFraction sigma Over epsilon EndFraction
where σ σ sigma\sigmaσsigma is stress , ε ε epsi\varepsilonεepsilon is strain
Elastic modulus 是表示stiffness的量. A material having a large elastic modulus is very stiff and difficult to deform.
There are three relationships, corresponding to tensile, shear, and bulk deformation, and all of them satisfy an equation similar to Hooke’s law for springs:
F = k Δ x F = k Δ x F=k Delta xF = k \Delta xF=kΔxupper F equals k normal upper Delta x

(胡克定律与超过弹性限制的状况)
The tensile strain in this case is defined as the ratio of the change in length Δ L Δ L Delta L\Delta LΔLnormal upper Delta upper L to the original length L 0 L 0 L_(0)L_0L0upper L 0 and is therefore a dimensionless quantity (任意方向都可). We can write an equation relating tensile stress to tensile strain:
F A = Y Δ L L 0 F A = Y Δ L L 0 (F)/(A)=Y(Delta L)/(L_(0))\frac{F}{A}= Y \frac{\Delta L}{L_0}FA=YΔLL0StartFraction upper F Over upper A EndFraction equals upper Y StartFraction normal upper Delta upper L Over upper L 0 EndFraction
In this equation, Y is the constant of proportionality, called Young’s modulus（就是E). Notice that the equation could be solved for F F FFFupper F and put in the form F = k Δ L F = k Δ L F=k Delta LF=k \Delta LF=kΔLupper F equals k normal upper Delta upper L, where k = Y A L 0 k = Y A L 0 k=(YA)/(L_(0))k = \frac{YA}{L_0}k=YAL0k equals StartFraction upper Y upper A Over upper L 0 EndFraction , making it look just like Hooke’s law.
It’s possible to exceed the elastic limit (弹性极限) of a substance by applying a sufficiently great stress.

总结：

Stress 应力:

σ = F A σ = F A sigma=(F)/(A)\sigma = \frac{F}{A}σ=FAsigma equals StartFraction upper F Over upper A EndFraction

Strain 应变:

ε = Δ L L 0 ε = Δ L L 0 epsi=(Delta L)/(L_(0))\varepsilon = \frac{\Delta L}{L_0}ε=ΔLL0epsilon equals StartFraction normal upper Delta upper L Over upper L 0 EndFraction
因为
